From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 11:59:19 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): journal state snapshots with crash-safe
 compaction (FR-E83)

Bound recovery-journal growth and replay cost with a `state_snapshot`
journal event plus a crash-safe compaction operation (engine-automatic
and CLI-manual) that truncates the replay prefix without weakening the
durability contract.

- Snapshot event carrying snapshot_version, full RunState, events_covered
- Single replayer extended: seed from latest valid snapshot + tail,
  forward-refuse unsupported versions, suffix-only replay, torn-tail
  tolerance after a snapshot; snapshot-free journals unchanged
- journal-compaction.ts: replay -> .tmp (one snapshot) -> fsync ->
  copy .bak (one generation) -> atomic rename; crash-safe at every step;
  refuses an active run or unreplayable journal (nothing modified)
- Config: defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events (default 1000,
  0 disables), validated; engine auto-compacts at node-completion
  (level) boundaries, one verbose line
- CLI: `runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <id> [--dry-run]` with the
  exact pinned summary line, refusals exit non-zero one-line, in --help
- Docs: FR-E83 in SRS execution-model + design recovery section + index

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
