+### 3.83 FR-E83: Journal State Snapshots with Crash-Safe Compaction
+
+- **Description:** Bounds the growth of the append-only recovery journal
+  (`journal.jsonl`, FR-E69) and its replay cost via a `state_snapshot` journal
+  event plus a crash-safe compaction operation (automatic in the engine,
+  manual via CLI) that truncates the replay prefix without weakening the
+  durability contract.
+
+  **Snapshot event:** A new journal event kind `state_snapshot` carries
+  `snapshot_version: 1`, the complete replayed run model (`RunState` — run
+  status/metadata, per-node statuses/facts, declared nodes, costs) and
+  `events_covered` (count of journal events the snapshot subsumes). It is an
+  ordinary enveloped journal line (`schema_version`, `run_id`, `seq`,
+  `event_id`, `ts`).
+
+  **Replay (single replayer, `run-journal.ts`):** Journals without any snapshot
+  replay exactly as before. When snapshots are present, replay seeds from the
+  LATEST valid snapshot and applies only events after it. A snapshot with
+  `snapshot_version` greater than supported fails replay with an error naming
+  the journal path and the unsupported version. For any run,
+  `state(snapshot + tail)` is byte-equal (JSON) to `state(full journal)`. Replay
+  of a compacted journal parses only the snapshot line plus subsequent lines.
+  The torn-trailing-line tolerance keeps working on compacted journals,
+  including a torn line immediately after the snapshot.
+
+  **Compaction protocol (engine + CLI share it), in exact order:** (1) replay
+  the current journal; (2) write `journal.jsonl.tmp` = one `state_snapshot`
+  followed by zero tail events; (3) fsync the tmp file; (4) copy the current
+  journal to `journal.jsonl.bak`; (5) atomically rename tmp over
+  `journal.jsonl`. A crash at every intermediate point leaves a journal that
+  replays (old content or new content, never neither). Compaction refuses
+  (clear error, nothing modified) when the run is active (lock held by a live
+  process) or the journal does not replay beyond the torn-line tolerance.
+  Exactly one `.bak` generation is kept and the summary mentions it.
+
+  **Engine integration:** Settings field
+  `defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events` (non-negative integer; `0`
+  disables auto-compaction; default `1000`). During a run the engine triggers
+  compaction at node-completion (level) boundaries only — never mid-node —
+  when the event count since the last snapshot exceeds the threshold, emitting
+  a single verbose line.
+
+  **CLI:** `flowai-workflow runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <runId>
+  [--dry-run]` performs manual compaction with the same protocol/refusal rules;
+  `--dry-run` prints event counts and byte sizes and modifies nothing; success
+  prints exactly `compacted <runId>: <eventsBefore> -> <eventsAfter> events,
+  <bytesBefore> -> <bytesAfter> bytes (backup: journal.jsonl.bak)`; run
+  not-found / refusal exit non-zero with a one-line error (no stack trace); the
+  subcommand appears in `--help`.
+- **Tasks:** [journal-snapshots-compaction](../tasks/2026/06/journal-snapshots-compaction.md).
+- **Dep:** FR-E69 (durable run journal replay — the replayer extended here);
+  FR-E54 (per-workflow run lock — active-run refusal signal).
+- **Acceptance criteria:**
+  - **Tests:** `snapshot-replay_test.ts`, `journal-compaction_test.ts`,
+    `config_test.ts`, `cli_test.ts` (FR-E83; regression-locked; snapshot
+    round-trip equivalence, suffix-only replay, torn line after snapshot, every
+    crash-injection point, both refusal cases, threshold config validation +
+    default, boundary-only auto-trigger, `--dry-run` no-op + exact summary).
+  - [x] `state_snapshot` event + latest-snapshot seeding + forward refusal in
+    the single replayer. Evidence: `src/state/run-journal.ts`
+    (`seedFromLatestSnapshot`, `buildStateSnapshotEvent`, `state_snapshot` apply
+    case).
+  - [x] Crash-safe compaction protocol with fault hook + refusal rules.
+    Evidence: `src/state/journal-compaction.ts` (`compactJournalCore`,
