+# engine: journal state snapshots with crash-safe compaction
+
+## Goal
+
+Bound the growth of the append-only recovery journal (`journal.jsonl`) and the
+cost of replaying it by adding a `state_snapshot` journal event plus a
+crash-safe compaction operation (automatic in the engine, manual via CLI) that
+truncates the replay prefix without ever weakening the durability contract.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+`run-journal.ts` is the single source of replay truth (FR-E69). Long runs append
+one fact per node/attempt/loop transition; the file and replay cost grow
+unbounded. A snapshot subsumes the replayed run model so replay can seed from
+the latest snapshot and apply only the tail.
+
+### Current State
+
+- `replayRunJournal(runDir)` parses every line, dedups by `event_id`, folds
+  events into a `RunState` via `applyJournalEvents`. Tolerates a torn final
+  line; throws on a malformed non-tail line.
+- `RunJournalWriter.open` continues after valid records, truncating a torn tail.
+- Engine threads one `RunJournalWriter` through node lifecycle; replays on resume.
+- No snapshot, no compaction, no size bound.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- The existing replayer in `src/state/run-journal.ts` is the single source of
+  replay truth — extend it; a second replayer is forbidden.
+- Journals without any snapshot MUST replay exactly as before (zero behaviour
+  change for old artifacts).
+- A snapshot with `snapshot_version` greater than supported MUST fail replay
+  with an error naming the journal path and the unsupported version.
+- Compaction follows EXACTLY this order: (1) replay; (2) write `journal.jsonl.tmp`
+  = one `state_snapshot` + zero tail; (3) fsync tmp; (4) copy journal →
+  `journal.jsonl.bak`; (5) atomic rename tmp over journal. A crash at every
+  intermediate point leaves a journal that replays (old or new, never neither).
+- Compaction refuses (clear error, nothing modified) when the run is active
+  (lock held by a live process) or the journal does not replay beyond the torn
+  tolerance.
+- Exactly one `.bak` generation is kept; the summary mentions it.
+- No new dependencies; reuse existing journal path/state helpers; follow the
+  existing `src/cli.ts` argument-parsing style.
+- `deno task check` stays green.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] (FR-E83) `state_snapshot` event kind added; payload carries
