+
+## Solution
+
+### Selected variant — B: Snapshot-in-journal + dedicated compaction module
+
+Rationale (autonomous benchmark selection): Variant B stores the full replayed
+`RunState` in a `state_snapshot` journal line and extends the existing replayer
+to seed from it — satisfying "snapshot is part of the journal format" and "single
+replayer" simultaneously. A dedicated `journal-compaction.ts` isolates the
+crash-safe protocol with a test-only fault hook and a reusable
+`maybeCompactAtBoundary` shared by engine + CLI. Variant A (inline everything in
+`run-journal.ts`) bloats one module and tangles the protocol with the replayer.
+Variant C (sidecar snapshot files + manifest, generational) is explicitly out of
+scope (snapshot must be in the journal format; exactly one `.bak`).
+
+### Files
+
+- `src/types.ts` — add `state_snapshot` to `RunJournalEventKind`;
+  `StateSnapshotJournalEvent`; add to `RunJournalEvent` union; add
+  `journal_compaction_threshold_events?` to `WorkflowDefaults`.
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` — `SUPPORTED_SNAPSHOT_VERSION = 1`;
+  `buildStateSnapshotEvent(runId, seq, state, eventsCovered)`; extend
+  `replayRunJournal` to find the latest snapshot, forward-refuse, slice the
+  suffix, seed in `applyJournalEvents` (`state_snapshot` case sets state);
+  `RunJournalWriter` tracks `eventsSinceSnapshot` (computed in `open`, bumped in
+  `append`, reset on snapshot append); expose `nextSeq` via a getter for compaction.
+- `src/state/journal-compaction.ts` (new) — `compactJournalCore(runDir, opts)`
+  (protocol + fault hook + replay-refusal), `compactRunJournal({workflowDir,
+  runId, dryRun})` (adds active-run refusal via `isRunLive`, run-not-found),
+  `maybeCompactAtBoundary({journal, runDir, runId, threshold, onCompacted})`
+  returning the (possibly reopened) writer. Types `CompactionStep`,
+  `CompactionSummary`.
+- `src/config/config.ts` — default `journal_compaction_threshold_events: 1000`
+  in `DEFAULT_WORKFLOW_DEFAULTS`; validate in the `defaults` block
+  (non-negative integer). Excluded from `extractNodeSettings` (workflow-only).
+- `src/engine/engine.ts` — after each level in `runWithLock`, call
+  `maybeCompactAtBoundary` with the resolved threshold, reassigning `this.journal`.
+- `src/cli.ts` — `runs` subcommand dispatch → `compact` parser + handler; help text.
+- Docs — new FR-E83 in `01-execution-model.md`; update design
+  `04-data-and-logic.md` journal/recovery bullet; `documents/index.md` FR row;
+  SRS back-pointer `**Tasks:**` bullet.
+
+### Approach notes
+
+- Snapshot payload = the `RunState` (exactly what replay reconstructs). The
+  equivalence invariant is asserted on the reconstructed `RunState` JSON (the
+  "replayed run model"); the replay-metadata `events` array intentionally differs
+  (compacted history is gone) and is not part of the run model.
+- Crash-safety holds because replay reads only `journal.jsonl`; `.tmp`/`.bak` are
+  side files. The `.bak` is written before the rename so a crash between copy and
+  rename still leaves the old `journal.jsonl` intact.
+- Engine auto-compaction uses `compactJournalCore` directly (the engine is the
+  lock holder coordinating at safe level boundaries — never mid-node, no parallel
+  race); the active-run refusal guards only the external CLI path.
+- `events_covered`/`eventsBefore` = replayed events length; `eventsAfter` = 1.
+
+### Error handling
+
+- Replay refusal: `compactJournalCore` replays first; a malformed non-tail line
+  throws out of `replayRunJournal` before any file write → nothing modified.
+- Active-run refusal: `compactRunJournal` checks `isRunLive` before touching files.
+- CLI wraps handler in try/catch → `Error: <msg>` one line, `Deno.exit(1)`; no stack.
+
+### Verification
+
+- `deno task check`
+- New tests: `src/state/snapshot-replay_test.ts`,
+  `src/state/journal-compaction_test.ts`; extended `src/config/config_test.ts`,
+  `src/cli_test.ts`.
